go to town
Homonym Number:
Word Class: phrase
Sense Number:
Definition:to become angry or excited, to go to market; to play up


Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: [none]
Region: [none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: ca1945 used often in Wellington, and in Marlborough e.g. He went to town when he saw the mess. I'll go to town on him if he does it again
